      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "July 3rd, 1870\n\nStanding adorned upon Velind's soot-blackened soil, I gaze upon our primitive societies dancing — a grotesque spectacle reminiscent of savagery. Their incessant clamor dares not concern my thinking; only British law and method could extinguish such obnoxious chaos. Arranging communities with the precision of clockwork, prohibiting such customs as untamed fires at festival feasts and blood rituals, I find solace in our Anglican overseers. I am the cat over the mouse, a light unto the benighted peoples with my import of Western morality and order, shepherding them away from their dark morass with the unwavering hand of progress and science. My role is to shepherd not just the menial but their very souls — an orderly flock under the vast rule of Britannia. Their salvation lies within my law, my faith, my domain, for only under the gleaming banner of the sun do I watch them burn their way to enlightenment.",
      "source": "target",
